TO MAKE THE MISO HONEY SYRUP: Combine @miso{25%g}, @honey{200%g}, and @water{150%g} in a small sauce pot. Stir gently and heat over medium-low heat until warmed throughâ€”do not boil. You just want enough warmth to allow the honey and miso to blend and dissolve together. Once cooled, store in the refrigerator.

TO MAKE THE DAIQUIRI: Add @miso honey syrup{1.5%oz}, @lime juice{0.5%oz}, @pineapple juice{0.75%oz}, and @aged rum{4%oz} to a #cocktail shaker{} filled with ice. Shake vigorously until well chilled. Double strain into a #stemmed glass{} and garnish with a fresh pineapple leaf.